I've always had trouble driving R/C vehicles just because it's a bit difficult for me to quickly adjust my sense of direction to match the orientation of the vehicle itself. Like if I'm flying an R/C helicopter and I turn it to face left relative to myself, I instinctively push left on the control stick but that makes it fly towards me instead of going to my left (the helicopter's forward) and then I panic for a moment trying to avoid getting hit by the thing and just lose control. I think if I had one with a front facing camera, like a lot of drones do nowadays, and I had that feed on the controller itself or in a visor, I'd have a much easier time controlling R/C vehicles.
